            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1640087229677-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the leek and shallot are slightly softened, add the <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong>, <strong>drained butter beans</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper </strong>and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped thyme </strong>and <strong>bay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span></strong></p><p>Give everything and good mix up and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
